values: Notes: First of all, congratulations to Katou for his upcoming Budoukan live! Second, regarding this blog, I won't deny that I've moved on from the Tenimyu fandom. However, I wouldn't say that I have completely forgotten Katou Kazuki -- who can ever forget this handsome hunk of a man amirite? -- and it's not at all fair to the rest of you if I abandoned this translation diary altogether. That said, I herely declare A REVIVAL of this blog. Unfortunately, I don't have the time to go through all past entries and translate backlogs as I had intended to, but I will certainly post translations of new entries from here on. Thank you for your patience, all of you. Last but not least, have Katou's latest entry: October 13: The best night My~! Time truly passes in the blink of an eye. To think that the Hibiya Nouto live that I've been looking forward to so much is already over... It really was a dream-like moment. But because it wasn't a dream but a reality, I shall carve this day on my breast and walk towards the next stage. To everyone who came today, thank you for the greatest battle!! Let's meet at the next tour, and the Budoukan!

June 12: Brings back memories... Recently I cleaned up my room. Curiously, in the midst of cleaning, nostalgic items came out one after another. First is "Doubu's forest". Lately I haven't been doing that at all (-.-;) When I consider how many cockroaches originated... And what came out next was a picture of me when I was young. Even though I say that it was the time when I was about 20 (laugh) Even so, I thought, I clearly changed alot~ I always say this but, time truly passes by in the blink of an eye. The things that I thought about as though I had considered them yesterday as well, now they seem like something very long ago. But I still remember them all freshly. Looking at past photos, this moment today is when once again, I felt that I'll live on and treasure everything day by day. I think I'll live and treasure the idle day tomorrow as well. June 13: To everyone who always supports me Everyone, thank you for supporting me, always. This time, starting with music, in order to widen my activities, it has been arranged that I'll move to avex. The move to avex has large meaning for me. Of course, I have worries but, the hope in my heart rises far more than that. I think that all the things that I haven't done till now, and the things I've never thought about, will surface one by one. Quite a bit of time has passed from the 1st Anniversary Live of my debut at Shibuya Koukaidou (CC Lemon) but, from now on, I'd like to work hard with new emotions. I'm confident that I can give everyone more enjoyment and shock than before. Things that change and things that don't... even though my activities change, I will continue to exist as Katou Kazuki. Everyone, please continue to support me from now on. And, please look forward to my activities from here on. June 13: Just how much~?? Today, I had an experience that may happen only once in a lifetime. That is, meeting the same person by coincidence twice in one day. And that person's name is... Itou Yousuke. The whom I acted with in bambino2 as Ryouta, he was the one and only member who was the same age as me. First, in the midst of a photoshoot for a magazine, we met on the roadside!! The second time was at Theatre Apple (laugh) !!! Plus, here, he was together with the people I worked with for bambino, Takeo-san, Yoshida-san There are such coincidences huh~ (*_*) Maybe you just haven't realised it, but you may have actually passed by the same acquaintance several times in one day... [note: There should be more tomorrow; I'll catch up again soon, thanks for your patience, everyone!]

Notes: Hiatus until finals are over, which is about May 8-ish. I apologise for the wait, but I promise a full batch out by the end of May at the very least. To all who are going through hell week as well, good luck!

[May 14 entry]

Stage Performance
Having entered the middle of May, it has started to become humid. The live held on the 5th could be thought as something that happened quite a long time ago.
After the live was over and I've calmed down a little, I went to see two of my friends' performances. As it forced me to think of stage performances, it was good stimulation. The day before that, I went to see the ROCK'N'JAM Musical that Takuya and Kouji are in. They're different from how they usually are, and it gave a strange feeling but, it was a really good performance. The sound being limited to a raw production. Their strength is different! I thought, I wanted to stand on that stage too.
If I continue to have free time, I'd like to watch various more stage performances.
